In <CA8LLt.63n@versant.com> Joe Keane <jgk@versant.com> writes:

>I asked the same question about hash functions a while back.  No one seemed to
>have much to say except that they didn't see any problem.

>I don't see much difference between these things.  Good hash functions and
>random number generators share many of the same principles as good encryption
>functions.  And it's pretty easy to turn one into another.

I suspect it's not what you call or claim it to be, it's what other people use
it for.

If I remember right, the compression on some modems (most 14.4k's for example)
is considered encryption, and that's just compression...

I'm not a lawyer, and I don't play one here.  :)

